must get a lot of offers.

524
00:44:32,294 --> 00:44:34,505
I guess there's no going back.

525
00:44:34,588 --> 00:44:35,464
Whatever the reality,

526
00:44:36,924 --> 00:44:38,676
it's about how we feel.

527
00:44:43,639 --> 00:44:45,474
Dr. Cha watched all along.

528
00:44:47,017 --> 00:44:49,937
He watched you for the whole year.

529
00:44:50,020 --> 00:44:50,979
Dr. Cha did?

530
00:44:52,064 --> 00:44:53,315
What?

531
00:45:25,347 --> 00:45:26,473
Was this photoshopped?

532
00:45:27,349 --> 00:45:28,392
By whom?

533
00:45:29,226 --> 00:45:30,269
Dr. Heo did.

534
00:45:51,248 --> 00:45:52,916
PAIN MANAGEMENT CENTER

535
00:46:18,358 --> 00:46:19,443
What?

536
00:46:19,526 --> 00:46:21,361
You've known all along?

537
00:46:22,112 --> 00:46:25,032
Do you think he wouldn't have called me
for the whole year?

538
00:46:25,115 --> 00:46:26,408
I knew everything.

539
00:46:27,117 --> 00:46:29,453
-You did?
-Then was the crying an act?

540
00:46:30,329 --> 00:46:32,748
Gosh, I got goosebumps.
You could be an actor.

541
00:46:32,831 --> 00:46:35,000
Why didn't you tell us?

542
00:46:35,083 --> 00:46:37,836
He was still being treated,

543
00:46:37,920 --> 00:46:39,630
and he exercised so hard.

544
00:46:40,255 --> 00:46:42,257
He only recently regained his health.

545
00:46:43,342 --> 00:46:45,427
But he always had you on his mind!

546
00:47:24,299 --> 00:47:25,133
Dr. Cha.

547
00:47:31,932 --> 00:47:36,061
I just couldn't forget you.

548
00:47:38,063 --> 00:47:41,567
I couldn't find anyone like you.

549
00:47:52,828 --> 00:47:54,246
Don't leave anymore.

550
00:47:55,289 --> 00:47:56,790
Don't go anywhere.

551
00:47:57,749 --> 00:47:59,585
Stay by my side.

552
00:48:11,972 --> 00:48:12,806
I will.

553
00:48:16,643 --> 00:48:17,477
Kang Si-young,

554
00:48:18,604 --> 00:48:19,688
I love you.

555
00:49:07,069 --> 00:49:08,195
No cucumbers, please.

556
00:49:15,994 --> 00:49:17,829
-Enjoy your meal.
-Thanks.

557
00:49:33,553 --> 00:49:34,388
KANG SI-YOUNG

558
00:49:34,471 --> 00:49:35,389
I'm so late!

559
00:49:40,018 --> 00:49:40,852
Stay strong.

560
00:49:41,520 --> 00:49:44,147
KANG SI-YOUNG

561
00:50:01,248 --> 00:50:02,124
Hello?

562
00:50:03,667 --> 00:50:04,918
I'm nearby.

563
00:50:05,002 --> 00:50:06,628
I'll be right there.

564
00:50:13,427 --> 00:50:14,886
Hello.

565
00:50:21,768 --> 00:50:23,854
-It has been a while.
-It has.

566
00:50:34,239 --> 00:50:35,866
Under the current law,

567
00:50:35,949 --> 00:50:38,243
we can put a stop to unnecessary
life-prolonging treatment.

568
00:50:39,077 --> 00:50:41,955
Since the law regards life,
rather than permitting,

569
00:50:42,748 --> 00:50:44,583
the focus should be on limiting.

570
00:50:44,666 --> 00:50:47,294
That limiting could obstruct
the right not to be in pain.

571
00:50:48,086 --> 00:50:51,089
Supplying nutrients and drugs
sometimes even postpones death.

572
00:50:51,173 --> 00:50:53,216
An increase in the scope of those rights

573
00:50:53,300 --> 00:50:55,469
could turn society into one
that forces death.

574
00:50:55,552 --> 00:50:59,181
Before hasty and drastic changes,
our society must first

575
00:50:59,264 --> 00:51:02,559
gain a more mature awareness
of death itself.

576
00:51:03,643 --> 00:51:05,562
Everyone here respects life,

577
00:51:05,645 --> 00:51:08,774
which is why no one should give up easily,

578
00:51:08,857 --> 00:51:12,861
or left to suffer in pain for too long.

579
00:51:12,944 --> 00:51:17,532
I believe that hospice and
palliative care is neutral ground.

580
00:51:17,657 --> 00:51:22,788
Yes. What terminal cancer patients
need the most is not treatment,

581
00:51:22,871 --> 00:51:25,665
but care. Being looked after.

582
00:51:25,749 --> 00:51:28,418
Yes. I agree with that.

583
00:51:29,503 --> 00:51:32,172
For terminally ill patients,
the end of their lives

584
00:51:33,215 --> 00:51:34,174
isn't dying.

585
00:51:35,634 --> 00:51:38,553
It must be to live while death approaches.

586
00:51:47,270 --> 00:51:48,605
Are you back for good?

587
00:51:49,606 --> 00:51:50,440
Yes.

588
00:51:51,066 --> 00:51:53,652
The painkiller you developed.

589
00:51:53,735 --> 00:51:55,529
Will I be able to use it one day?

590
00:51:55,612 --> 00:51:57,155
Our center is waiting for it too.

591
00:51:57,823 --> 00:51:59,366
I hope it helps.

592
00:52:01,785 --> 00:52:02,994
How are you?

593
00:52:03,870 --> 00:52:06,832
I don't know how much time I have left,

594
00:52:07,874 --> 00:52:09,793
but I'm living just fine.

595
00:52:16,550 --> 00:52:17,843
See you again.

596
00:52:18,718 --> 00:52:19,845
Sure.

597
00:52:20,345 --> 00:52:21,680
We will.

598
00:52:23,223 --> 00:52:25,308
Dr. Cha said no?

599
00:52:27,227 --> 00:52:28,061
Why?

600
00:52:28,770 --> 00:52:32,315
He doesn't think
he must remain at our center.

601
00:52:32,399 --> 00:52:34,234
Many other doctors can do that.

602
00:52:36,361 --> 00:52:40,157
If the drug he developed
is commercialized,

603
00:52:40,240 --> 00:52:41,825
we'll be able to use it.

604
00:52:44,828 --> 00:52:46,705
If that were to happen,

605
00:52:46,788 --> 00:52:49,249
I wouldn't envy having 100 doctors
like him.

606
00:52:53,211 --> 00:52:55,964
The doctors are on their way.
Hang in there.

607
00:53:00,760 --> 00:53:01,970
-Help her up.
-Okay.

608
00:53:06,474 --> 00:53:07,851
Take this medicine.

609
00:53:18,403 --> 00:53:19,654
What is this?

610
00:53:19,738 --> 00:53:21,698
The 24-hour brainwave test showed

611
00:53:21,781 --> 00:53:23,700
clear epileptic waves
when your stomach hurt.

612
00:53:23,783 --> 00:53:26,411
You have abdominal epilepsy.

613
00:53:26,494 --> 00:53:29,664
The anti-seizure medicine
will dull the pain.

614
00:53:29,748 --> 00:53:33,543
We'll have to see,
but the serious symptoms will go away.

615
00:53:34,753 --> 00:53:36,338
Then am I free now?

616
00:53:37,088 --> 00:53:40,217
The medicine will help you
go about your everyday life.

617
00:53:43,053 --> 00:53:44,638
Thank you, Doctor.

618
00:53:45,931 --> 00:53:46,765
Thank you.

619
00:53:57,067 --> 00:53:58,902
Did you talk to Dr. Cha yesterday?

620
00:54:00,403 --> 00:54:01,279
Yes.

621
00:54:02,197 --> 00:54:04,115
Sorry for not telling you for a year.

622
00:54:04,950 --> 00:54:06,868
Mi-rae told me off real bad.

623
00:54:08,245 --> 00:54:10,205
You said Dr. Cha asked.

624
00:54:11,164 --> 00:54:12,249
I understand.

625
00:54:12,999 --> 00:54:14,167
Thank you.

626
00:54:15,585 --> 00:54:18,004
If he didn't have you to talk to,

627
00:54:18,088 --> 00:54:20,131
he'd have been so lonely.

628
00:54:23,551 --> 00:54:25,637
Did you hear where he works now?

629
00:54:26,471 --> 00:54:28,473
-Yes.
-Shall we all visit one day?

630
00:54:29,849 --> 00:54:30,767
After you.

631
00:54:31,726 --> 00:54:32,644
Let's go.

632
00:55:00,547 --> 00:55:02,048
We're almost there.

633
00:55:02,132 --> 00:55:03,800
WE'RE ALMOST THERE

634
00:55:10,140 --> 00:55:16,104
HEALING CLINIC

635
00:55:20,650 --> 00:55:23,153
I told you not to,
but you smoke in secret.

636
00:55:25,864 --> 00:55:27,574
When will you quit?

637
00:55:28,241 --> 00:55:30,118
You always complain about pain. Lie down.

638
00:55:30,785 --> 00:55:31,911
Did you pee well?

639
00:55:32,662 --> 00:55:33,913
-Yes.
-Good.

640
00:55:37,167 --> 00:55:38,626
What?

641
00:55:40,628 --> 00:55:42,297
WE'RE ALMOST THERE

642
00:55:43,089 --> 00:55:44,174
I'm a doctor.

643
00:55:44,257 --> 00:55:46,176
What did you say?

644
00:55:47,218 --> 00:55:50,013
To those awaiting death
at the end of their lives,

645
00:55:50,972 --> 00:55:54,559
what they need more than
painkillers that no longer work…

646
00:55:54,642 --> 00:55:56,311
I see your nipples.

647
00:55:56,394 --> 00:55:59,689
is someone who
understands their suffering.

648
00:56:01,107 --> 00:56:03,943
Don't skip your meals
and exercise is a must, okay?

649
00:56:04,027 --> 00:56:05,653
Goodbye, sir.

650
00:56:05,737 --> 00:56:06,654
And…

651
00:56:06,738 --> 00:56:08,239
No smoking.

652
00:56:08,323 --> 00:56:11,951
The comfort that their pain is
shared by someone.

653
00:56:12,035 --> 00:56:13,370
HEALING CLINIC

654
00:56:13,453 --> 00:56:15,163
His cancer has spread to his larynx,

655
00:56:15,246 --> 00:56:17,665
so his voice is damaged.
How can you understand him so well?

656
00:56:17,749 --> 00:56:19,125
-Hi.
-Hi.

657
00:56:19,834 --> 00:56:21,711
I can't understand him well either,

658
00:56:21,795 --> 00:56:23,922
but I just try my best.

659
00:56:24,839 --> 00:56:28,426
Who knows if what he said today
could be his last words?

660
00:56:30,345 --> 00:56:32,472
-Dr. Cha!
-Dr. Cha!

661
00:56:32,555 --> 00:56:33,598
Guys!

662
00:56:36,434 --> 00:56:37,477
Welcome.

663
00:56:42,273 --> 00:56:44,901
Where should we start?
I'm sure there's a lot to do around here.

664
00:56:44,984 --> 00:56:46,820
In Hanse Wish Club,

665
00:56:46,903 --> 00:56:49,531
we've been getting many certificates
and receiving a lot of training.

666
00:56:49,614 --> 00:56:51,199
We're good at cleaning and doing laundry.

667
00:56:51,282 --> 00:56:53,660
Can I go around the ward
and take wishes from the patients?

668
00:56:53,743 --> 00:56:56,079
You can do whatever you want.
I won't stop you.

669
00:56:56,162 --> 00:56:57,372
Start!

670
00:56:57,455 --> 00:56:58,331
Let's go!

671
00:57:13,847 --> 00:57:15,306
Let's go this way.

672
00:57:18,726 --> 00:57:20,812
Sir, you look so stiff.

673
00:57:20,895 --> 00:57:22,313
Try to put on a big smile.

674
00:57:23,064 --> 00:57:24,357
Here we go.

675
00:57:24,441 --> 00:57:26,734
One, two, three.

676
00:57:26,818 --> 00:57:27,652
One more.

677
00:57:28,486 --> 00:57:29,737
What's your name?

678
00:57:30,488 --> 00:57:31,823
Relax.

679
00:57:35,201 --> 00:57:36,619
This might sting a little.

680
00:57:36,703 --> 00:57:40,123
Let me check your blood-sugar level.
Give me your hand.

681
00:57:52,886 --> 00:57:53,970
Are you okay?

682
00:57:54,053 --> 00:57:55,638
It hurts.

683
00:58:01,311 --> 00:58:03,188
Let me play a song on the piano for you.

684
00:58:03,271 --> 00:58:04,731
I'm not that good, but please listen.

685
00:58:05,523 --> 00:58:06,774
It's a fun song.

686
00:58:07,775 --> 00:58:08,818
All right.

687
00:58:14,407 --> 00:58:16,326
Pain is the proof of life.

688
00:58:17,952 --> 00:58:19,746
Pain lives inside us.

689
00:58:20,371 --> 00:58:23,333
Our lives come to an end with pain.

690
00:58:27,754 --> 00:58:30,715
Having someone next to you
to share your pain with

691
00:58:31,382 --> 00:58:32,926
reduces your pain

692
00:58:33,760 --> 00:58:36,888
and gives you the courage
to embrace your pain.

693
00:58:50,568 --> 00:58:53,780
Recognizing and sharing
someone else's pain.

694
00:58:55,031 --> 00:58:58,910
That is my last prescription
for our pain that stays with us

695
00:59:00,370 --> 00:59:02,705
for as long as we live.

696
01:00:18,906 --> 01:00:23,911
